body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/445\n\n## Problem\nIn a tag-heavy workspace ~43% of `pm context` brief output (1970 of 4582 B) is repeated `tags:` blocks — siblings inherit the parent tag set and repeat it verbatim per row. No --no-tags; brief depth cannot drop tags.\n\n## Proposed fix\n(1) `--no-tags` on context (and honor --fields projection, shipped via PR#297); (2) inherited-tag folding: when all low_level children share the parent tag set, emit tags once on the parent (or `tags_inherited: true`); (3) consider tag-less rows as the brief-depth default.\n\n## Definition of done\nContext size in this workspace cut ~40% at brief depth with no loss for the next-work decision; spec pins folding semantics; MCP pm_context parity; docs updated."
